<div id="review_116739176" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/116739176" />
    <a title="Melissa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3973903-melissa"><img alt="Melissa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1591224885p2/3973903.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/116739176?book_show_action=true">Aug 14, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Melissa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Melissa" href="/user/show/3973903-melissa">Melissa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3973903-melissa?shelf=didnt-finish">didnt-finish</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3973903-melissa?shelf=series">series</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3973903-melissa?shelf=arc">arc</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer116739176" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer88954449284518735">The cover is the best part of the book. I really wanted to like this book. I&apos;ve always liked reading books with angels in it, but this book was so bad that I had to finally give up after around 270 pages because I couldn&apos;t stand it anymore. <br/><br/>The beginning was okay, but after that, it was so long and draggy and I was getting ticked off by Bethany. Her sudden [and most of the time irrational] mood-swings and clinginess to Xavier, and general helplessness really made me not like her. I mean, what ty</span>
  <span id="freeText88954449284518735" style="display:none">The cover is the best part of the book. I really wanted to like this book. I've always liked reading books with angels in it, but this book was so bad that I had to finally give up after around 270 pages because I couldn't stand it anymore. <br /><br />The beginning was okay, but after that, it was so long and draggy and I was getting ticked off by Bethany. Her sudden [and most of the time irrational] mood-swings and clinginess to Xavier, and general helplessness really made me not like her. I mean, what type of angel are you if you always depend on other people to save the day?<br /><br />I haven't read a book this bad in a long time; I wouldn't even recommend it to a middle schooler because the main character is such a terrible role model for girls [helpless damsel in distress]. <br /><br />Time to read something better like <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7260188.Mockingjay__Hunger_Games___3_" title="Mockingjay (Hunger Games, #3) by Suzanne Collins" rel="nofollow noopener">Mockingjay</a>.</span>
  <a data-text-id="88954449284518735" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


