<div id="review_97940392" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/97940392" />
    <a title="April" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1405910-april"><img alt="April" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1574686846p2/1405910.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/97940392?book_show_action=true">Apr 10, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="April" class="user" itemprop="url" name="April" href="/user/show/1405910-april">April</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1405910-april?shelf=ya">ya</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1405910-april?shelf=for-review">for-review</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1405910-april?shelf=paranormal">paranormal</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1405910-april?shelf=bea-2010">bea-2010</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1405910-april?shelf=angels">angels</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer97940392" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10465212419652565773">It&apos;s interesting how the phrase don&apos;t judge a book by it&apos;s cover works both ways. Sometimes an ugly book cover contains a beautiful story. Sometimes a gorgeous cover cloaks mediocre work. When I grabbed a copy of Halo at BEA, it was like getting a golden ticket. Halo was one of my highly anticipated reads. I mean, look at the awesome cover! However, I wound up incredibly disappointed.<br/><a href='http://www.goodbooksandgoodwine.com/2010/08/review-of-halo-by-alexandra-adornetto.html' rel='nofollow noopener'>Read the rest of my review here</a></span>
  <span id="freeText10465212419652565773" style="display:none">It's interesting how the phrase don't judge a book by it's cover works both ways. Sometimes an ugly book cover contains a beautiful story. Sometimes a gorgeous cover cloaks mediocre work. When I grabbed a copy of Halo at BEA, it was like getting a golden ticket. Halo was one of my highly anticipated reads. I mean, look at the awesome cover! However, I wound up incredibly disappointed.<br /><a href="http://www.goodbooksandgoodwine.com/2010/08/review-of-halo-by-alexandra-adornetto.html" rel="nofollow noopener">Read the rest of my review here</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="10465212419652565773" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

